  "text": "Although the majority of YFP-CSI1 2012-2150 labeled cortical compartments were immobile (Supplemental Movie 4), a few of them displayed microtubule-shrinking end tracking behaviors Figure 3C ; Supplemental Movie 6). CSI1 has been previously shown to associate with CESA in SmaCCs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Our data indicate that the C2 domain of CSI1 might be involved in the association of CSI1 and CESA in SmaCCs/MASCs.",
